{"article_id":"1VObIYZo6NWxT6Dl","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Ted Cruz accomplished","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"what he set out to do in the Wisconsin Republican primary :","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"beat front-runner Donald Trump soundly ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"winning most of the state ' s delegates","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"and raising the probability of a contested GOP convention in July .","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"But Senator Cruz ' s big victory","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"- he beat Mr. Trump by 13 points , 48 percent to 35 percent -","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"doesn ' t prove","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"that he is \" uniting the Republican Party , \"","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"as he claimed in his victory speech Tuesday night .","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"It merely demonstrates","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"that the Texas senator is consolidating his role as the \" anti-Trump \" in a presidential nomination race","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"that has plunged the GOP into crisis .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"\" More than half of Cruz ' s supporters , and two-thirds of [ Ohio Gov . ] John Kasich ' s , said","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"they were ' scared ' of what Trump would do in the White House","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"- a remarkable rejection of the leading candidate in the race , \"","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"write analysts for ABC News .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"\" Notably , among Cruz ' s own voters , only a quarter were excited about what he ' d do as president","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"- further suggesting","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that he garnered substantial anti-Trump , not necessarily , pro-Cruz , support . \"","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Governor Kasich underperformed in Wisconsin with only 14 percent of the vote ,","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"but he remains adamant about taking his campaign to the convention as the only \" mainstream \" Republican still in the race .","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"The effect , though , has been to split the anti-Trump vote .","depth":5},{"id":23,"text":"Perhaps more troubling for the GOP were responses to how Wisconsin Republicans would vote in the general election .","depth":5},{"id":24,"text":"If Trump is the party ' s nominee against Democrat Hillary Clinton ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"only 61 percent of GOP primary voters said","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"they would vote for him ;","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"19 percent said","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"they would vote for a third-party candidate ,","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"10 percent said","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"they would vote for Mrs. Clinton ,","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"and 8 percent said","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"\" no one . \"","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"If it ' s Cruz vs. Clinton in November ,","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"only 66 percent of Wisconsin Republicans said","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"they ' d back Cruz ;","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"18 percent said","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"they ' d vote third party ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"6 percent said Clinton ,","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"and 6 percent said","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"\" no one . \"","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"These numbers are similar to national polling","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"that shows a deep divide within the GOP between Trump supporters and Republican voters","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"who oppose him .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"It ' s also true that , inevitably ,","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"as Election Day nears ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"many unhappy voters will surely end up holding their nose","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"and voting for their party ' s nominee anyway .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"Clinton , in particular , inspires revulsion among many Republicans .","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"But Trump is no mere Republican candidate .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"The brash billionaire inspires rock-solid loyalty among a third of the GOP electorate , including the first-time voters","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"he has lured into the process with his populist , nativist message .","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"If Trump is not the nominee ,","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"many of his supporters say ,","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"they will abandon the party altogether -","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"especially if they believe","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"Trump is treated unfairly at the convention .","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"On the issue of \" fairness , \" one exit poll question was particularly devastating to the Republican establishment :","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"If no one wins a majority of the delegates before the convention ,","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"whom should the party nominate ?","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"voters were asked .","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"A majority , 55 percent , said","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"\" the candidate with the most votes in the primaries. \"","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"Only 43 percent said","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"\" the candidate","depth":15},{"id":65,"text":"who","depth":17},{"id":66,"text":"the delegates think","depth":17},{"id":67,"text":"would be the best nominee . \"","depth":16},{"id":68,"text":"\" In all likelihood , Donald Trump will go to the convention with the most delegates .","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"Wisconsin doesn ' t really change that , \"","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"says Matthew Kerbel , chairman of the political science department at Villanova University in Philadelphia .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"If Trump arrives at the convention","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"without a majority of the delegates ,","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"then it becomes easier to deny him the nomination .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"\" But the cost","depth":15},{"id":75,"text":"of denying him","depth":15},{"id":76,"text":"is to split the party , \"","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"says Professor Kerbel .","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"\" And the cost","depth":15},{"id":79,"text":"of not denying him","depth":15},{"id":80,"text":"is it becomes his party ,","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"and Donald Trump becomes the face of the party . \"","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"That could have a profound impact on other Republicans on the ballot .","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"Among general election voters , Trump has sky-high negatives .","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"Cruz and Clinton also have high negatives","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"- but not close to Trump ' s .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"Kasich argues","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"he ' s the most electable ,","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"and general election matchups bear that out ,","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"but his path to the nomination through a contested convention is impossibly narrow .","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"He ' ll need to convince a deadlocked convention","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"that a candidate","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"who finished at the back of the pack","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"deserves to jump the line .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"His argument is \" electability \" -","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"polls do show him performing better than Trump or Cruz against Clinton .","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"But Tuesday ' s exit polls showed","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"electability held little sway with voters .","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":99,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":100,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":101,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":102,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":103,"text":"The next test comes in two weeks with the New York primary","depth":2},{"id":104,"text":"- home turf for both Trump and Clinton ,","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"who , like Trump , needs to overcome an embarrassing defeat in Wisconsin .","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"Clinton ' s 13-point loss to Bernie Sanders","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"- 56 to 43 percent -","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"was nevertheless expected .","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Wisconsin ' s electorate is largely white , and very liberal ,","depth":6},{"id":110,"text":"both playing to the Vermont senator ' s strengths .","depth":6},{"id":111,"text":"Trump also wasn ' t a good fit for Wisconsin , both demographically and culturally .","depth":4},{"id":112,"text":"Before Wisconsin , New York polls showed both Trump and Clinton well ahead of their top competitors .","depth":6},{"id":113,"text":"If either underperforms ,","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"it will be clear that Wisconsin was a turning point .","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"Both will be damaged ,","depth":6},{"id":116,"text":"but still on track","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"to head to their respective conventions with the most delegates .","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"The math , at this stage in the race , is almost impossible to overcome .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":237,"left":221,"right":236,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":221,"left":216,"right":220,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":216,"left":141,"right":215,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":138,"right":140,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":131,"right":137,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":123,"right":130,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":123,"left":120,"right":122,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":2,"right":121,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":121,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":130,"left":127,"right":129,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":127,"left":124,"right":126,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":7,"right":125,"rel